events.name: Cloud Study Jam

venue.name: Website Desgn and Development, Graphics Design and Video Production, and Elearninig center

events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but
don't know where to begin? Join us for our
Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free
of charge. Together we'll work through several
Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on
experience with the Cloud Console,
Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and
Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free
access to more labs you can finish at home.
Complete all labs in the quest and earn a
Google-hosted badge for your online profile,
and additional 30 days access to the training
platform to compete any labs you want.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or
Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest
versions of the popular browsers. For the best
experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or
Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

events.name: Flutter Study Jam I

venue.name: Website Desgn and Development, Graphics Design and Video Production, and Elearninig center

events.description:
Flutter Study Jam
Flutter Study Jam is Where Participants learn how to use flutter to develop high-quality interactive applications for IOS, Android devices and Web applications. Study Jam are great opportunity to brings members of our Community together to learn some amazing things.

About Flutter
Flutter is Google's mobile SDK for crafting high quality native interfaces on IOS, Android, web. Flutter also works with Existing code, is used by organization and developers around the World and its free and Open Source

Wanna learn Flutter??

Join us for our GDG Adama Flutter Study Jam! Together We will introduce our self to Amazing flutter in and outs and work some thing Really cool.

What do you need??

Bring your own Laptop and it's better if Flutter is installed prior to starting the study Jam to save up some time.
Windows/Mac/Linux
https://flutter.dev/get-started/install/

When? and Where?

June 1 , 2019 from Morning Local Time 3 - 6
At Adama science and Technology University

events.description:
I/O Extended events help developers from around the world take part in the I/O experience. In 2018, developers hosted more than 500 I/O Extended viewing parties around the world and many more joined online. I/O Extended events span the world, connecting the global developer community.

Please join us to explore the latest developments in Google technology.

upcoming.name: DevFest Adama 2019

venue.name: Website Desgn and Development, Graphics Design and Video Production, and Elearninig center

upcoming.description:
DevFest (Developers Festival) is an annual community-run event that offers keynote speakers who are very influential, speaker sessions across multiple product areas, including hack-a-thons, codelabs, and more.

This is a gathering of developers and technology enthusiasts to cover multiple product areas such as Android, Firebase, Android Things, Kotlin, Flutter, Google Cloud Platform, ARCore, Google Assistant, Design Sprint, IoT, Machine Learning, Mobile Web and Artificial intelligence.
